            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>It is possible, especially on Detroit Diesel Series 60 engines to over-tighten the A/C compressor
                    belt. The nature of the belt and the A/C compressor arrangement on Series 60 engines make it
                    difficult to properly tension the belt. If the A/C compressor belt on a Series 60 engine is
                    tensioned to the installation tension of 150 to 180 lbs, followed by tightening of the compressor
                    mounting bolts, the tension can rise above 180 lbs, possibly as high as 400 lbs.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="0">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <para>In order to obtain a final installation tension of 150 to 180 lbs, do the following:</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Ensure compressor mounting bolts are approximately finger tight.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a Poly "V" belt tension gauge on belt. Turn tension adjustment bolt until
                    tension of 150 to 180 lbs is reached.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Retighten compressor mounting bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">After the mounting bolts are tightened, the tension should be rechecked with a belt
                    tension gauge to ensure the tension is still within the 150 to 180 lbs. range.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">After engine operation, the belt tension should be approximately 120 lbs.</para>
            </step1>
            <para>There is some confusion on belt tension for ribbed Poly "V" and standard "V" belts. A
                <hotlnk xrefid="t9612231">Belt Installation Tension Chart</hotlnk>
                that lists both installation and operating belt tensions for most Navistar applications is included with
                this TSI.
            </para>
